<br>
Before I start I want to make clear that I do support giving newbies FS weapons and other items that drop and are not usable at my level.  However its the begging part that I personally cant stand.<br>
<br>
Newbie Beggar:  Hey there sir (You look rich), can I trouble you for some help.<br>
<br>
Kaitan:  Okay ... how can I help you??<br>
<br>
Newbie Beggar:  Can you please please please give me some platinum or a magic weapon cause I dont have anything.<br>
<br>
Kaitan: (Reaches into his bag) Just a sec ... I think I might have something for ya!<br>
<br>
Kaitan gives one froglock tongue to Newbie Beggar.<br>
<br>
Newbie Beggar:  Ummm thanks ....<br>
<br>
Newbie Beggar:  Whats this for??<br>
<br>
Kaitan: Thats the tongue of the last  Beggar who asked me for free *Stuff*(edited for content)!!!<br>
<br>
Newbie Beggar: Thats mean ... You should be nicer to us newbie beggars!!!<br>
<br>
Kaitan: Well I'm a Dark Elf Shadow Knight and am Evil to the Core you are lucky I dont kill you right now!!!<br>
<br>
Kaitan steps into the shadows.<br>
<br>
Role Playing the Newbie Beggars is in my opinion the best way to teach them how to play the game and not spend their time begging for free stuff.<br>
<br>
Thoughts, Experiences, Comments....?<br>
